
** Set Transaction

  - SQL> set transaction name 'abc';
  - SQL> set transaction set isolation level commited 'abc';

** Autonomous Transactions

  - This type of transaction is not nested. It's not rollbacked if
    the main transaction rollbacks.

  <example>
    declare
      PRAGMA AUTONOMOUS_TRANSACTION;
    ...
    end;
  </example>

  - Triggers that uses AT can perform DDL statements.

** User Transactions

  - v$transaction

  - To join with v$session use the TADDR from v$session

** All Transactions

  - v$rollstat

** DDL Statement

  - DDL statement are using the system rollback segment.

